refactor: split monolithic flat files into multi-file package structure

Comprehensive architecture refactor of DevHive IDE Android app.

## What changed
- Deleted 15 old flat-file Kotlin sources from com.example root
- Created proper sub-package hierarchy with 31 new files

## New package layout
- data/model/AppModels.kt      — OllamaModel, ChatMessage, AgentStep, ShellLine/Type, ChatSegment, MdSegment, AppTab
- data/api/OllamaApi.kt        — Ollama HTTP client (moved, same content)
- data/api/LlamaCppApi.kt      — llama.cpp HTTP client (moved, same content)
- agent/AgentEngine.kt         — ReAct loop (slim version)
- agent/tools/                 — FileTools, BashTool, WebTool, SearchTools, MemoryTool, ToolExecutor
- ui/components/CommonComponents.kt
- ui/editor/CodeEditor.kt      — EnhancedCodeEditor + getFileIcon/getLanguageFromExtension
- ui/home/HomeScreen.kt        — MainAppScreen + bottom nav
- ui/server/ServerScreen.kt
- ui/models/ModelsScreen.kt
- ui/chat/ChatScreen.kt + MarkdownViewer.kt
- ui/agent/AgentScreen.kt, AgentChatPane.kt, AgentFilesPane.kt, AgentStepsPane.kt
- ui/terminal/TerminalScreen.kt  — includes formatFileSize()

